verbose_text: We further showed that knockdown of SNAP23 and/or SNAP25 leads to accumulation of Tfn and TfnR at the cell periphery and suppresses fusion of Tfn-TfnR-containing recycling vesicles with the PM; these phenotypes resemble those exhibited by Rab11-, Exo70- or Sec15-knockdown cells shown in our previous study.
evidence: SNAP23 and/or SNAP25 leads to accumulation of Tfn and TfnR at the cell periphery and suppresses fusion of Tfn-TfnR-containing recycling vesicles with the PM
